{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17599005","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17599005"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:47:50+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:47:50+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15518"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15518","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15518"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.95,0,0,0.05,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8209"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64355"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8209","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8209"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15518"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49787"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4927"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"9895"},{"type":"tags","id":"9897"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19862"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19865"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64355","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/64355"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EPulmonary fibrosis is characterised by the replacement of normal lung tissue with fibrous connective tissue, leading to changes in lung mechanics and volumes.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following changes occurs in pulmonary fibrosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Decreased compliance","Increased total lung capacity","Increased functional residual capacity","Increased residual volume","Increased vital capacity"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EIn pulmonary fibrosis, the replacement of normal elastic lung tissue with stiff fibrous tissue leads to \u003Cstrong\u003Edecreased compliance\u003C/strong\u003E. This means the lungs become less distensible and require more force to inflate.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe stiff lungs also result in reduced lung volumes, not \u003Cstrong\u003Eincreased total lung capacity\u003C/strong\u003E, \u003Cstrong\u003Eincreased functional residual capacity\u003C/strong\u003E, \u003Cstrong\u003Eincreased residual volume\u003C/strong\u003E, or \u003Cstrong\u003Eincreased vital capacity\u003C/strong\u003E. All lung volumes are typically decreased in restrictive lung diseases like pulmonary fibrosis due to the reduced ability of the lungs to expand.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Pulmonary fibrosis decreases lung compliance due to stiff, scarred lung tissue","Lung volumes are uniformly decreased in pulmonary fibrosis due to reduced tissue elasticity"],"references":["Mason, R. J., Broaddus, V. C., Martin, T. R., King, T. E., Schraufnagel, D., Murray, J. F., \u0026 Nadel, J. A. (2010). Murray and Nadel\u0027s textbook of respiratory medicine E-book: 2-volume set. Elsevier Health Sciences.","Sankari A, Chapman K, Ullah S. Idiopathic Pulmonary Fibrosis. [Updated 2024 Apr 23]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK448162/","Zisman DA, Keane MP, Belperio JA, Strieter RM, Lynch JP 3rd. Pulmonary fibrosis. Methods Mol Med. 2005;117:3-44. doi: 10.1385/1-59259-940-0:003. PMID: 16130230; PMCID: PMC7120641.","Noth I, Cottin V, Chaudhuri N, Corte TJ, Johannson KA, Wijsenbeek M, Jouneau S, Michael A, Quaresma M, Rohr KB, Russell AM, Stowasser S, Maher TM; INMARK trial investigators. Home spirometry in patients with idiopathic pulmonary fibrosis: data from the INMARK trial. Eur Respir J. 2021 Jul 8;58(1):2001518. doi: 10.1183/13993003.01518-2020. PMID: 33419890; PMCID: PMC8264778."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49787"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15518"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49787","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/49787"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-23T13:29:08+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-23T13:29:32+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8209"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64355"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4927","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4927"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec1","name":"Respiratory","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2024-10-17T23:14:59+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-31T0